 President Muhammadu Buhari (middle) with General Superintendent of Deeper Life Bible Church, Pastor William Folorunso Kumuyi (left), and his wife,<br />Esther, during their visit to the Presidential Villa in Abuja…yesterday.  “My morale is raised by your visit. I very much appreciate it,’’ he stated.The president noted that “God did not make a mistake when he created over 250 different ethnic groups and decided to put them in a place called Nigeria.’’He therefore urged Nigerians to appreciate God for bringing everyone together. Buhari said he was “excited a great deal’’ for the cleric’s acceptance of government’s invitation to preach at the country’s 58th independence anniversary. Kumuyi told his host that he appreciates the government. “Please remain focused and courageous and do what is right. Not everyone will support you publicly, but we are praying for you so that your tenure will be one of progress and prosperity for the country,’’ the cleric added. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .